  pricingCompetitor="From $79/mo"
  pricingNote="Starting at $79/mo for 2,000 subscribers. No free tier."
  faqs={[
    {
      question: "Is DigiStorms cheaper than Encharge?",
      answer: "Yes. DigiStorms starts free for up to 100 new signups per month, with paid plans from $19/mo. Encharge begins at $79/mo for 2,000 subscribers with no free option. For early-stage SaaS teams, DigiStorms is the more budget-friendly choice that still delivers AI-powered onboarding sequences.",
    },
    {
      question: "Which has better automation features?",
      answer: "Encharge offers a powerful visual flow builder with granular behavior triggers, lead scoring, and 50+ integrations. DigiStorms takes a different approach — instead of building flows manually, the AI generates your onboarding sequence automatically based on your product. If you want full manual control, Encharge wins. If you want automation that works out of the box, DigiStorms is faster.",
    },
    {
      question: "Can DigiStorms replace Encharge for onboarding emails?",
      answer: "For onboarding-specific email sequences, yes. DigiStorms is purpose-built for SaaS onboarding and generates behavior-triggered emails automatically. However, Encharge also handles newsletters, lead scoring, and broader marketing automation. If your primary need is onboarding emails, DigiStorms is a focused and more affordable alternative.",
    },
    {
      question: "How long does setup take for each tool?",
      answer: "DigiStorms gets you live in about 5 minutes. You enter your website URL, the AI analyzes your product, and it generates a complete onboarding sequence. Encharge requires you to manually design flows, set up triggers, write emails, and configure integrations — which typically takes hours to days depending on complexity.",
    },
    {
      question: "Which is better for a SaaS startup?",
      answer: "For most startups, DigiStorms is the better starting point. It has a free tier, gets you live in minutes, and handles onboarding emails automatically. Encharge is a strong choice once you outgrow basic onboarding and need complex multi-step automations, lead scoring, and extensive integrations across your marketing stack.",
    },
  ]}
/>
